<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12127f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12127f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12127f"> 127(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Trinity in host?</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Entre les deux th&eacute;ologiens <font color="green">[Vincent Ferrier and a man named Nicolas Eymeric]</font>, la brouille commen&ccedil;a sans doute &agrave; propos de l&apos;incident suivant. Les cur&eacute;s de Valence avaient pris l&apos;habitude de pr&eacute;senter l&apos;hostie aux malades en leur demandant s&apos;ils croyaient que le P&egrave;re, le Fils et le Saint-Esprit y &eacute;taient pr&eacute;sents. Que la Trinit&eacute; interv&icirc;nt ainsi dans l&apos;Eucharistie, cela parut suspect &agrave; Eymeric. Il &eacute;crivit de savants m&eacute;moires, adressa des reproches v&eacute;h&eacute;ments. Ce fut sans r&eacute;sultat. Les cur&eacute;s continu&egrave;rent leurs pratiques. C&apos;est alors que saint Vincent Ferrier intervint. Il &eacute;dicta quelques r&egrave;glements concrets et simples et apaisa le conflit comme en se jouant. <br><font color="green">[Between the two theologians the fight must have started with the following incident. The parish priests of Valence had the habit of presenting the host to the sick while asking them if they believed that the Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost were present in it. <mark>That the Trinity was involved in the Eucharist</mark> seemed to Eymeric very suspect. He wrote learned treatises, reproached them vehemently. Without result. The priests continued their practice. This is when Vincent Ferrier intervened. He created a few concrete and simple rules and appeased the conflict as if playing.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 27</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
